### Paper Summary
The paper proposes a dataset-centric active learning framework for flow matching models with continuous conditions (for aerodynamic shape design). It models the velocity network as a CPWL interpolator to derive a diversity-accuracy trade-off, yielding two antagonistic query strategies ($Q_D$, $Q_A$) and a hybrid weighting mechanism.

