- Missing compute analysis, somewhat contradictory results in some benchmarks
- DISTAR is stronger: has subjective evaluation, ablations on CFG/patch size, and a cleaner narrative
- Both fail to properly isolate the contribution's value relative to simpler alternatives

---

### Dimension-by-Dimension Assessment

| Dimension | Score |
|---|---|
| **Novelty** | Moderate-to-high — discrete masked diffusion over RVQ with hybrid AR is genuinely novel; "tail-first" bias identification is a new insight |
| **Technical soundness** | Moderate — sound design but efficiency claims run at NFE=24 vs. baselines at NFE=10/32 with no RTF; no component ablations |
| **Empirical support** | Moderate — comprehensive metrics (WER, SIM, UTMOS, CMOS, SMOS) against modern baselines, but SIM=0.67 trails E2TTS=0.70 while claiming speaker consistency superiority |
